

# --------------------
# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# Closes: #<issue number>
# Signed-off-by: Your Name <your.email@example.com>
#
# --- COMMIT END ---
# Type can be
#   feat:     new feature
#   fix:      bug fix
#   refactor: refactoring code
#   style:    formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change
#   docs:     changes to documentation
#   test:     adding or refactoring tests
#   chore:    updating build tasks, package manager configs, etc
# --------------------
# Remember to:
#   - Use the present tense ("Add feature" not "Added feature")
#   - Use the imperative mood ("Move cursor to..." not "Moves cursor to...")
#   - Limit the first line to 72 characters or less
#   - Reference issues and pull requests liberally after the first line
# --------------------
#
# --- Quick Examples ---
#  feat(auth): add password reset functionality
#  fix(ui): correct button alignment on mobile devices
#  docs(api): update endpoint documentation
#  style(global): format code with prettier
#  refactor(utils): simplify date formatting logic
#  perf(db): add index to improve query performance
#  test(auth): add unit tests for login flow
#  build(webpack): update build configuration
#  ci(github): add automated deployment workflow
#  chore(deps): update dependencies to latest versions
#  revert: revert "feat(user): add avatar upload"
#  --------------------
